The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Lady cop cries molestation
                                                                                                               Lady cop cries molestation
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Oct. 4: A woman constable at Jarada police station in Ganjam district has accused the inspector in charge of sexual harassment and molestation.        
	The victim, Rajeswari Nayak, registered her complaint with the Berhampur superintendent of police, R.K. Sharma, alleging that Trinath Mishra attempted to rape her while she was on duty.        
	Rajeswari also alleged that her FIR was not being accepted and she was forced to submit it to the Sharma.         
	The woman complained that she was being repeatedly harassed by her senior and whenever she opposed she was misbehaved publicly.        
	Mishra, who has gone on leave, has rebuffed the allegations terming them baseless and calling it a conspiracy to tarnish his image.        
	The constable and havildar association of Ganjam today met Sharma and demanded a stern action against the accused.        
	A sub-divisional police officer is inquiring into the constables allegation, said Sharma.                                                                                                                                                                            
